    "id": "f_csv_37e20f2afe",
    "slug": "as-a-perfume-doth-remain-in-the-folds-where-it-hath-lain-so-the-thought-of-you",
    "texto": "As a perfume doth remain In the folds where it hath lain, So the thought of you, remaining Deeply folded in my brain, Will not leave me; all things leave me -You remain. Other thoughts may come and go, Other moments I may know That shall waft me, in their going, As a breath blown to and fro, Fragrant memories; fragrant memories Come and go. Only thoughts of you remain In my heart where they have lain, Perfumed thoughts of you, remaining, A hid sweetness, in my brain. Others leave me; all things leave me -You remain.",
    "autor": "Arthur Symons",
    "autorSlug": "arthur-symons",
